---
import ProjectLayout from "../../components/ProjectLayout.astro";
import TechIcon from "../../components/TechIcon.astro";
---

<ProjectLayout
  title="Endava — Enterprise Consulting"
  description="Case study: 3 years of full-stack JS across Deutsche Telekom, NETS Scandinavia, and eLife Sciences"
>
  <main>
    <section
      class="project-hero"
      style="background: var(--dark); color: white; padding: 5rem 0 3.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; text-align: center; position: relative;"
    >
      <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px;">
        <h1
          style="font-size: 3rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; letter-spacing: -0.02em;"
        >
          Endava — Enterprise Clients
        </h1>
        <p
          style="font-size: 1.35rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto 2rem; line-height: 1.6;"
        >
          Nearly 3 years of full-stack JavaScript across Deutsche Telekom,
          NETS Scandinavia, and eLife Sciences — the foundation for everything after
        </p>
        <div
          style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;"
        >
          <span
            style="padding: 0.5rem 1.25rem; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); border-radius: 50px; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.85rem; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.15);"
          >
            AGENCY
          </span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <article style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px;">

      <!-- THE CONTEXT -->
      <section
        class="content-section"
        style="background: var(--gradient-card); border-radius: 20px; padding: 3rem 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);"
      >
        <h2
          style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--dark);"
        >
          The Context
        </h2>
        <p
          style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--gray); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;"
        >
          Endava is a global technology consultancy that places engineers with major
          enterprise clients. Over nearly 3 years there, I rotated across projects for
          Deutsche Telekom, NETS (Scandinavian payments infrastructure), and eLife Sciences
          (UK academic publishing) — all full-stack JavaScript.
        </p>
        <p
          style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--gray);"
        >
          This was the period that raised my bar. Working across telecoms, payments, and
          academic publishing forced me to adapt fast, learn new domains quickly, and deliver
          consistently regardless of the business context. It set the standard for the
          freelance and enterprise work I did afterward.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- THE WORK -->
      <section
        class="content-section"
        style="background: var(--gradient-card); border-radius: 20px; padding: 3rem 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);"
      >
        <h2
          style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 2rem; color: var(--dark);"
        >
          What I Built
        </h2>

        <div
          class="features-grid"
          style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 2rem;"
        >
          <div
            style="padding: 2rem; background: rgba(99,102,241,0.03); border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid rgba(99,102,241,0.08);"
          >
            <h3
              style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--primary);"
            >
              Scientific Paper Processing
            </h3>
            <p style="color: var(--gray); font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-style: italic;">eLife Sciences (UK)</p>
            <p style="color: var(--gray); line-height: 1.6;">
              Built a document conversion system with Node.js, AWS S3, and Lambda
              that processed 2,000+ scientific papers daily. The React frontend handled
              paper submission, tracking, and collaborative workflows — optimized for
              rendering large document collections without choking the browser.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div
            style="padding: 2rem; background: rgba(99,102,241,0.03); border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid rgba(99,102,241,0.08);"
          >
            <h3
              style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--primary);"
            >
              E-Commerce Checkout System
            </h3>
            <p style="color: var(--gray); font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-style: italic;">NETS Scandinavia</p>
            <p style="color: var(--gray); line-height: 1.6;">
              Created a checkout system with React and TypeScript supporting multiple
              payment methods including Klarna and traditional cards. In payments,
              reliability isn't a nice-to-have — every edge case in the flow is someone's
              money. This is where my attention to payment-critical code started.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- BUSINESS IMPACT -->
      <section
        class="content-section"
        style="background: var(--gradient-card); border-radius: 20px; padding: 3rem 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);"
      >
        <h2
          style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--dark);"
        >
          Impact Across Clients
        </h2>

        <div
          class="metrics-grid"
          style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr)); gap: 2rem; margin: 2.5rem 0;"
        >
          <div
            style="text-align: center; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(99,102,241,0.05); border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid rgba(99,102,241,0.1);"
          >
            <div
              style="font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"
            >
              2K+
            </div>
            <div style="color: var(--gray); font-weight: 500;">
              Papers Processed Daily
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            style="text-align: center; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(99,102,241,0.05); border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid rgba(99,102,241,0.1);"
          >
            <div
              style="font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"
            >
              3
            </div>
            <div style="color: var(--gray); font-weight: 500;">
              Enterprise Domains (Telecom, Payments, Academic)
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            style="text-align: center; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(99,102,241,0.05); border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid rgba(99,102,241,0.1);"
          >
            <div
              style="font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"
            >
              2
            </div>
            <div style="color: var(--gray); font-weight: 500;">
              Junior Devs Mentored
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- WHAT I LEARNED -->
      <section
        class="content-section"
        style="background: var(--gradient-card); border-radius: 20px; padding: 3rem 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);"
      >
        <h2
          style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--dark);"
        >
          What I Took Away
        </h2>
        <p
          style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--gray); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;"
        >
          Agency work forces you to get productive fast in unfamiliar codebases and
          domains. After rotating through telecoms, payments, and academic publishing in
          under 3 years, I stopped being intimidated by new contexts. The pattern is
          always the same: understand the domain, find the real constraints, ship.
        </p>
        <p
          style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--gray);"
        >
          This is also where I started mentoring — guiding 2 junior developers through
          React best practices and Node.js architecture. Teaching others forced me to
          articulate what I knew and identify gaps in my own understanding. It made me
          a better engineer, not just a more senior one.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- TECH STACK -->
      <section
        class="content-section"
        style="background: var(--gradient-card); border-radius: 20px; padding: 3rem 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);"
      >
        <h2
          style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 2rem; color: var(--dark);"
        >
          Technology Stack
        </h2>
        <div
          style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(140px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem;"
        >
          {
            [
              { name: "React", tech: "React" },
              { name: "TypeScript", tech: "TypeScript" },
              { name: "Node.js", tech: "Node.js" },
              { name: "AWS Lambda", tech: "AWS" },
              { name: "AWS S3", tech: "AWS" },
              { name: "Klarna", tech: "JavaScript" },
            ].map((item) => (
              <div style="padding: 1.25rem 1rem; background: var(--dark); color: white; border-radius: 16px; font-weight: 600; text-align: center; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); transition: all 0.3s ease; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; min-height: 100px; justify-content: center;">
                <TechIcon technology={item.tech} size={32} />
                <span style="font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.2;">
                  {item.name}
                </span>
              </div>
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
</ProjectLayout>

<style>
  .project-hero h1 {
    color: white;
  }

  .content-section {
    animation: fadeInUp 0.6s ease forwards;
  }

  @keyframes fadeInUp {
    from {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(30px);
    }
    to {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }

  .features-grid > div:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
  }

  .content-section div[style*="min-height: 100px"]:hover {
    transform: translateY(-3px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 25px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .project-hero {
      padding: 48px 0 32px;
    }

    .project-hero h1 {
      font-size: 2.25rem;
    }

    .project-hero p {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
    }

    .content-section {
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
    }

    .metrics-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .features-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .content-section div[style*="repeat(auto-fill, minmax(140px, 1fr))"] {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(110px, 1fr)) !important;
      gap: 1rem !important;
    }

    .content-section div[style*="min-height: 100px"] {
      min-height: 80px !important;
      padding: 1rem 0.75rem !important;
    }

    .content-section div[style*="min-height: 100px"] span:first-child {
      font-size: 1.5rem !important;
    }

    .content-section div[style*="min-height: 100px"] span:last-child {
      font-size: 0.8rem !important;
    }
  }
</style>
